From 3833bc1fd7f8b47cb9e5609454e0753ad104dcd1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thiraviyam Mariyappan <tmariyap@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 22 May 2025 14:22:56 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] QSDK:DP:wifi: Allocate cachable memory and Avoid dma map
 unmap for IPQ5424

Allocate cachable memory for all the rings in IO coherency supported
platforms for the rings to enable fast data access and offload
related CMO operations to hardware.

Additionally, DMA map and unmap operation is not required for
IO coherency supported platform. So, avoid dma map coherent and dma
unmap coherent in driver.

Orginal patches:
985-01-QSDK-DP-wifi-Avoid-CMO-operation-for-IPQ5424.patch
985-02-QSDK-DP-wifi-Allocate-cachable-memory-for-IPQ5424.patch
985-03-QSDK-DP-wifi-Avoid-dma-map-unmap-for-IPQ5424.patch

Signed-off-by: Thiraviyam Mariyappan <tmariyap@qti.qualcomm.com>
